ThinkPart(
    type='think',
    think='Now I have a comprehensive understanding of the PR. Let me summarize 
my findings and create the review report.\n\nKey observations:\n\n1. **Backend -
NestJS:**\n   - `im.gateway.ts`: Follows the updated NestJS规范. Uses `JwtServic
e` instead of manual jwt.verify. Uses `@UsePipes(new ValidationPipe(...))`. Uses
`cors` in decorator instead of afterInit hack. ✅\n   - `im.controller.ts`: Now 
uses DTOs for query params (`GetConversationsQueryDto`, `GetMessagesQueryDto`). 
✅\n   - `im.service.ts`: \n     - Uses `EventEmitter2` for cross-module communi
cation (`match:created` event). ✅\n     - The `createSystemMessage` is called v
ia event listener, not inside the transaction - this follows the recommended pat
tern. ✅\n     - However, `getConversations` uses `.slice()` on arrays - wait, i
n TypeScript `.slice()` works on arrays. But I see `participants.slice(0, parsed
Limit)` - this is correct.\n     - Uses native SQL for last messages query with 
`?` placeholder. ✅\n     - Has `last_read_message_id` in response DTO but it\'s
not in the `ConversationResponseDto` type definition. Let me check... The DTO fi
le doesn\'t have `last_read_message_id`. The service returns it but the DTO does
n\'t define it. This is a minor inconsistency.\n     - Redis is imported via `Re
disModule` instead of creating a new instance. ✅\n   - `im.module.ts`: Imports 
`RedisModule`, `JwtModule`. ✅\n   - DTOs are properly separated into files. ✅\
n   - `send-message.dto.ts`: Uses `@ValidateIf((o) => o.type === "text")` for co
nditional validation. ✅\n\n2. **Flutter/Mobile:**\n   - `im_bloc.dart`: \n     
- App-level registration in `app.dart`. ✅\n     - Uses events for async callbac
ks (socket events map to `add()`). ✅\n     - Has cache limit enforcement (`_max
CachedMessages = 500`). ✅\n     - Has cross-session message buffering (`_pendin
gMessages`). ✅\n     - Connection state is embedded in `MessagesLoaded`, not se
parate state classes. ✅\n     - But `_onConversationUpdated` just calls `add(co
nst LoadConversations())` - this causes a full reload of the conversation list o
n every update, which is acceptable but not the most efficient.\n     - In `_onS
etCurrentConversation`, when merging pending messages, it uses `[...currentState
.messages, ...pending]` - but pending messages might need to be sorted by sequen
ce_id. If pending messages arrive out of order, they could be appended to the en
d while current messages might have higher sequence_ids. This is a potential iss
ue.\n     - `_onSendMessage`: Creates temp message with `senderId: null` - this 
should probably be the current user ID.\n   - `chat_page.dart`:\n     - Calls `I
mSetCurrentConversation(null)` on dispose. ✅\n     - Scrolls to bottom only on 
`MessageSent` and `isInitialLoad`. ✅\n     - Uses `Semantics` with proper ident
ifiers for Maestro. ✅\n     - Uses `GestureDetector(onTapDown: ...)` for Maestr
o compatibility. ✅\n     - `SwChatInputBar` doesn\'t pass `isSending` parameter
- but the BLoC does have `MessageSending` state. Minor issue.\n   - `im_socket_c
lient.dart`:\n     - Explicit reconnection config. ✅\n     - Uses `auth: {token
: token}`. ✅\n   - `match_list_page.dart`:\n     - Uses `BlocListener<ImBloc, I
mState>` to refresh conversation list on updates. ✅\n     - Good empty state ha
ndling. ✅\n   - `design-system`:\n     - Components are registered in `widgetbo
